Korpus Digital

* Coptic: Al-Ibsalmdiyya al-muqaddis as-sanawiyya, kopt.-arab., Ed. Kairo, o.J.;
  Euchologion, Kitb al-l al-muqaddis, kopt.-arab., Kairo, o.J.;
  Based on https://www.tasbeha.org with contribution of Dr. Michael Ghattas
* Islamic: Ed. Maktaba wa mabaa al-muallad al-arab, Cairo.;
  Ed. Dr as-Sulam l-ada, Marib.;
  Based on https://www.quranicaudio.com
* Mandaic:  E.S. Drower, Canonical Prayer Book of the Mandaeans, Leiden: E.J.  Brill, 1959, (Anhang) 4-494;
  Ed. J.H. Petermann, Thesaurus sive liber magnus liber vulgo Adami appellatus, 2 Bde., Leipzig, 1867, Bd. 2, 38-137.;
  Based on https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Qolasta with contribution of Dr. Bogdan Burtea
* Syriac East: Th. Darmo, Ktābā da-Qdam wa-d-Bātar wa-d-Ḥudrā wa-d-Kaškōl
  wa-d-Gazzā w-qālē d-‘udrānē ‘am ktābā d-mazmōrē. 3 Bd. Trichur, India:
  Mar Narsai Press, 1960-1962.
* Syriac West: G. Aydin (ed.), Syriac Hymnal, Beth Antioch Press, U.S. 2018;
  Stundengebete in: Awsā slāwōtʿō. The Book of Common Prayer, SEERI, Kottayam,
  Kerala, 2006. B. Varghese, West Syrian Anaphoras, Awsār Slāwōt’ō 4, SEERI,
  Kottayam, 2017.
